5 participate in the work-based learning program.
6 (c) A description of the process that will be used by pupils to apply to
7 participate in a work-based learning program.
8 (d) A description of the manner in which participation in a work-based learning
9 program and completion of the requirements of a work-based learning program will
10 be verified.
11 (e) A description of the manner in which the performance of a pupil who
12 participates in the work-based learning program will be evaluated, which must
13 include, without limitation, an on-site evaluation of the performance of the pupil.
14 3. Upon approval by the Superintendent of Public Instruction of an
15 application to offer a work-based learning program submitted pursuant to
16 subsection 2, the board of trustees or the governing body shall:
17 (a) Designate an employee of the school district or charter school, as
18 applicable, to serve as a work-based learning coordinator to coordinate and oversee
19 work-based learning programs. Such an employee must ensure that each business,
20 agency or organization that will offer employment and supervision of a pupil as
21 part of the work-based learning program is suitable for participation in a work-
22 based learning program.
23 (b) Establish and maintain a list of businesses, agencies and organizations that
24 have been found suitable by the work-based learning coordinator pursuant to
25 paragraph (a).
26 4. To receive approval from the Superintendent of Public Instruction to offer
27 a work-based learning program, the work-based learning program must include,
28 without limitation, requirements that:
29 (a) A detailed training agreement and training plan be completed for each pupil
30 participating in the work-based learning program for credit that identifies the
31 specific tasks in which the pupil will participate that will develop competency of
32 the pupil in the workplace;
33 (b) A pupil participating in the work-based learning program be allowed to
34 leave the public school in which he or she is enrolled during the school day to
35 participate in such a program;
36 (c) Participation by a pupil in the work-based learning program will develop a
37 broad range of skills and will allow a pupil to focus on his or her chosen career
38 pathway; and
39 (d) Training be completed by each pupil participating in the work-based
40 learning program on:
41 (1) Identifying and reporting harassment in the workplace;
42 (2) Developing and maintaining healthy relationships in the workplace;
43 and
44 (3) Identifying the signs of a person engaging in predatory conduct to
45 prepare a pupil for sexual activity or to foster an inappropriate personal or
46 professional relationship with a pupil, including, without limitation, through
47 communicating or attempting to befriend or establish a relationship or other
48 connection with a parent or legal guardian of a pupil in furtherance of such conduct.
49 5. A school district or charter school may allow a pupil who successfully
50 completes a work-based learning program to earn dual credit for participation in the
51 work-based learning program.
52 6. On or before January 15 of each odd-numbered year, the board of trustees
53 of a school district and the governing body of a charter school that offers a work-

